**Helper with Daily Life**
- Helping with bathing, dressing, and grooming
- Preparing meals and helping with eating
- Helping someone get around the house safely

**Medicine Manager**
- Making sure medicines are taken at the right time
- Keeping track of different medications
- Picking up prescriptions

**Appointment Coordinator**
- Scheduling doctor visits
- Taking notes at medical appointments
- Asking questions the doctors might not think to ask

**Emotional Supporter**
- Listening when your loved one needs to talk
- Providing comfort when they're scared or sad
- Keeping them company

**Safety Watcher**
- Making sure the home is safe
- Watching for signs that something is wrong
- Knowing when to call for help

**You Don't Have to Do Everything Alone**
Even though there are many jobs, you don't have to do all of them by yourself. Other family members, friends, and professionals can help share the work.`,
