- Emergence of role patterns

**Implementation Science**
- Translating effective interventions
- Addressing context and adaptation
- Sustainability of caregiver support programs

**Health Equity**
- Disparities in role preparation and support
- Cultural variations in role expectations
- Socioeconomic factors affecting role performance

**Care Integration Research**
- Family caregivers as care team members
- Communication platforms
- Shared decision-making models
- Quality improvement involvement

## Clinical Practice Recommendations

**Assessment Protocol**
1. Identify and document caregiver
2. Assess current role demands
3. Evaluate preparedness and training needs
4. Screen for role strain indicators
5. Provide tailored education and support
6. Establish follow-up monitoring

**Training Standards**
- Competency-based skill verification
- Return demonstration requirement
- Written materials with teach-back
- Video resources for complex tasks
- 24/7 contact for questions
- Home health follow-up for high-acuity needs

**System-Level Interventions**
- Caregiver-inclusive rounds
- EHR caregiver documentation
- Automated needs assessments
- Referral pathways to support services
- Quality metrics tracking`,
